  <description type="morphology">Plants 0.4–0.8 cm. Stem leaves spreading and somewhat twisted when dry, irregularly spreading and indistinctly 3-ranked when moist, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, 2–3.5 mm; base decurrent; margins plane to weakly reflexed basally, entire; apex acute to narrowly obtuse; costa narrow, ending in or just before apex; inner laminal cells smaller, walls thicker than those of marginal cells. Sexual condition synoicous. Seta 5–11 cm. Capsule 3.5–4.5 mm. Spores 36–44 µm.</description>
